00:49:41,286 --> 00:49:42,548
She's always...

292
00:49:44,789 --> 00:49:46,450
...wanted to see you.

293
00:49:51,729 --> 00:49:53,697
She was glad...

294
00:49:55,900 --> 00:49:57,060
...she finally did.

295
00:50:07,112 --> 00:50:08,306
Yeah?

296
00:50:14,719 --> 00:50:16,277
She was?

297
00:50:28,600 --> 00:50:29,760
Ah, that's good!

298
00:50:32,470 --> 00:50:33,630
Real good!

299
00:50:34,706 --> 00:50:38,164
For the first time in my life...

300
00:50:38,776 --> 00:50:40,607
...I told a white lie.

301
00:50:42,847 --> 00:50:46,578
A 'red lie' is one you tell for your own sake.

302
00:50:48,486 --> 00:50:52,718
A 'white lie' is one you tell for someone else's.

303
00:50:55,326 --> 00:50:59,285
That seems to be the gateway to adulthood.

304
00:51:54,686 --> 00:51:55,812
Tadashi!

305
00:51:57,188 --> 00:51:58,018
Yeah?

306
00:51:58,823 --> 00:52:02,554
Take out the garbage. I'll leave it here.

307
00:52:06,130 --> 00:52:09,156
I won't need dinner tonight.

308
00:52:09,267 --> 00:52:12,168
It's Mr. Yamada's farewell party.

309
00:52:12,737 --> 00:52:13,761
All right.

310
00:52:15,673 --> 00:52:16,799
I'm off, then.

